body:
As you must know, Riot updated Varus&#039; lore with an incredible music video clip, and it was just what I and lots of other LGBT people needed. 
At first, Riot didn&#039;t just piked a random champion and said that he was gay to call for attention, it was a part of a well developed story where the gays being a homosexual was just a detail. And that&#039;s awesome because we are so so much more then that.
Secondly, the love. We&#039;ve been fighting for the right for love and being loved for so long, and we have such a long way to go, although we just got equal marriage approved  in Australia there are so many places that our love is illegal. And Riot made it so beautiful how their love is giving Kai and Val power to fight against the Darkin, and protect the world fro it. Love is that powerful, and gay love is not different
Last but not least, League of Legends is one of the most played games in the world, and this incredible message is traveling to places that people are not even allowed to talk about it.
Well done and thank you so much Riot! I&#039;m looking forward  to the next LGBT champ!!!
